The Chinese Consulate-General in San Francisco confirmed on Thursday that five Chinese citizens were among the seven farmworkers killed in two related shootings in the coastal city of Half Moon Bay, California, just south of San Francisco. "We strongly condemn this incident of gun violence, and express our deep condolences to the victims and sincere condolences to the injured," the consulate-general said in a release, adding it is in communication with relevant U.S. departments to follow up on the investigation.